homestead.nodes.description: Nodes can be unlocked for your homestead and home instance. They can be collected once per day.
homestead.garden-plots.description: You can unlock up to three Garden Plots in your homestead.
homestead.garden-plots.crops.description: These are the different crops that can be planted in the garden plots. Varietal seed pouches can be crafted by Chefs after obtaining the Garden Plot Deed from the Gourmet Training achievement. Black Lion crops can be obtained for free from the Gardener NPC when owning at least one Black Lion Garden Plot.
homestead.cats.description: You can unlock these cats for your homestead and home instance.
homestead.decorations.description: These are the decorations you can unlock for your homestead.
homestead.glyphs.description: These glyphs can be slotted in the collection boxes in your homestead.
homestead.materials.description: Cost of refining materials for your homestead. There is a weekly limit for refining materials, which can be increased by purchasing Trade Capacity upgrades.

raids.description: Raids are difficult 10-player PvE instances. Each raid wing has weekly rewards for clearing it, which you can track in the table below if you are logged in. Each week one wing is emboldened, effectively reducing the difficulty, and one has the Call of the Mists effect, doubling the amount of gold earned.

festival.wintersday.intro: Bells are ringing, snowballs are flying, and Toymaster Tixx’s fantastic golem-shaped airship is hovering over Divinity’s Reach—the traditional Tyrian celebration of Wintersday is here again!
festival.wintersday.description: Keep track of your progress on all your accounts during Wintersday on gw2treasures.com.

festival.lunar-new-year.intro: The annual Lunar New Year festival is in full swing in Divinity’s Reach! Tyrians are celebrating the beginning of the Year of the Snake with fireworks, games, delicious Canthan food, and prizes.

festival.super-adventure.intro: Asuran genius Moto is bringing his high-tech invention, the Super Adventure Box, back for a yearly festival! Get ready to jump into the box and collect power-ups, test your bouncing skills, challenge Lord Vanquish, and collect bauble bubbles to exchange for rewards.

festival.dragon-bash.intro: Tyrians held the first Dragon Bash after Zhaitan’s defeat—an expression of relief and joy at beating impossible odds. Celebrate your victories with a grand party!

festival.four-winds.title: Festival of the Four Winds
festival.four-winds.intro: The Festival of the Four Winds returns! A collaborative effort by Her Royal Majesty Queen Jennah of Kryta, the Zephyrites, the Lionguard, and even the Black Lion Trading Company, this annual festival brings summertime fun and excitement to Tyria.

legendary-armory.relics.title: Legendary Relics
legendary-armory.relics.description: Legendary Relics can take the effect of any unlocked relic, and can be used on every character once unlocked in the Legendary Armory.
legendary-armory.relics.unlocks.descript: Core relics can always be used with the Legendary Relic. Other relics require the corresponding expansions, and relics introduced after Secrets of the Obscure have to be unlocked.
